(1, 5, 'How Tech Changes the Living Status of Man', '1~how-tech-changes-the-living-status-of-man', '<p><strong>The growth of technology is a continuous process in the current world. As such, many people make good use of it to make ends meet. Besides, some misuse tech, which leads to unwanted results. For instance, some use technology to acquire wealth, but in the wrong manner. As such, there is an increase in online fraud. Today, we will learn about the importance of technology in our day to day life. With that, it will be easier for one to determine how well they can use tech to their advantage but in the recommended manner. Read on through this article to find out more about that!&nbsp;</strong></p>', 'T7uF53xAUNWZCbZHSNjBEvf3k.jpg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:15:51', '2020-01-20 03:15:51'),
(2, 6, 'The Advent of Mind-Reading Is Here', '2~the-advent-of-mind-reading-is-here', '<p><strong>With new products made available on display at CES 2020 in Las Vegas, tech devices that use brain waves to improve sleep, anxiety, and concentration -- and even control prosthetic hands -- may finally be made effective.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Companies are focusing on the \"Brain-Computer Interface\" with devices that can record brain signals from sensors on the scalp (or even devices implanted within the brain) and translate them into digital signals. They allow us to connect our minds to computers for some limited purposes, and big tech companies including Facebook and many startups want to make this technology commonplace.</strong></p>', '2vQaNrTQT6w8F7sQLhUEAIpkg.jpeg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:17:49', '2020-01-20 03:17:49'),
(3, 7, 'Renewable Power Sources in UK Outstrips Fossil Fuels in 2020', '3~renewable-power-sources-in-uk-outstrips-fossil-fuels-in-2020', '<p><strong>The National Grid figures show a dramatic shift within the last 20 years. Hydropower, wind farms, and solar panels now generate just over a quarter of Britain\'s electricity, compared with 2.3 percent in 1990. Atomic power accounts for 17%, compared with nearly 20% in 1990. However, the utilization of gas - a fuel - also shot up to get quite 38% of the country\'s electric power last year, compared with just 0.1% in 1990.</strong></p>', 'Eg6PSQeazlOIMU8kv4Lvx3dHU.jpg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:19:02', '2020-01-20 03:19:02'),
(4, 8, 'NSA Finds Major Windows 10 Security Flaw', '4~nsa-finds-major-windows-10-security-flaw', '<p><strong>The aforementioned vulnerability is found in a decades-old Windows cryptographic component, known as CryptoAPI. One function is it allows developers to digitally sign their software, proving that the software has not been tampered with.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>This is a departure for the NSA from its past strategy of keeping security flaws under wraps to exploit for its own intelligence needs.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>During a press conference on Tuesday, they said the \"serious vulnerability\" could be used to create malicious software that appeared to be legitimate.</strong></p>', 'S3du2qaGLF8PuKNYm0mYmS5h9.jpg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:21:29', '2020-01-20 03:21:29'),
(5, 5, '5 Ways Families Can Save Energy', '5~5-ways-families-can-save-energy', '<p><strong>Use can make a huge difference in your home\'s energy output. A smart thermostat will help you more easily adjust your home\'s temperature. You can schedule the thermostat to lower when you leave home for work and raise when it\'s time for you to arrive back home. Smart thermostats even give you the ability to adjust the temperature from your phone. With the right programmable device, you\'ll notice a huge difference in the amount of energy your home uses. You can save energy with . You can even use a smart home device to program all the electronics in your home, from your alarm clock to your lightbulbs. Having the ability to customize your energy output can do wonders for your bills and the earth.</strong></p>', 'faQTLMjs3OvyPhDZQReyoRUiU.jpg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:23:55', '2020-01-20 03:23:55'),
(6, 6, 'Thailand Is Using Drones to Spray Pollution Away', '6~thailand-is-using-drones-to-spray-pollution-away', '<p><strong>Drones have largely become more prominent in their use in solving modern problems. From easy transportation of goods picking up the workload left by the effects of climate change and deforestation, drones hold a lot of potential for innovative strategies to limit the negative impacts on the environment.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>So it seems possible for the same easily-maneuvered autonomous vehicle to be utilized as a countermeasure to air pollution.</strong></p>', 'cAlJbslrnPT3SjQTCss188Hdl.jpg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:25:28', '2020-01-20 03:25:28'),
(7, 7, 'How Artificial Intelligence Improves the Quality of Data Mapping', '7~how-artificial-intelligence-improves-the-quality-of-data-mapping', '<p><strong>Customers are the holy grail of businesses. Organizations attempting to grow or expand are on a constant lookout for ways to reach more and more customers. Regular marketing campaigns, that were once considered relevant, don\'t have a colossal kind of impact now.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>In order to increase your customer base and beat your competition, you often need to market directly to the source, especially if you cater to the millennial generation.&nbsp;</strong></p>', 'xrEjRpuCqpGlAjNJceJ6sanUD.jpg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:26:58', '2020-01-20 03:26:58'),
(8, 8, 'Are Free Employee Time Tracking Software Really Free?', '8~are-free-employee-time-tracking-software-really-free', '<p><strong>Since most free employee time tracking software options are a part of the paid software, it shouldn\'t come as a surprise that their functionalities are usually limited. The packages are often separated in three tiers - free, and two paid options.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>With the free one, you can get a couple of basic features, which can be more than enough for you (depending on what you want from the software). However, you shouldn\'t expect that you can integrate the software with any type of project management or payment tools, or any other tools for that matter.</strong></p>', 'aTVTABjwu7uR5sPBZCDqfjgsW.jpg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:28:15', '2020-01-20 03:28:15'),
(9, 6, 'The Future of Sustainability and Ecotourism in Brisbane', '9~the-future-of-sustainability-and-ecotourism-in-brisbane', '<p><strong>A particularly vital part of this is protecting the Great Barrier Reef. The world\'s largest living structure is a World Heritage Area and one of the seven natural wonders. It\'s no surprise that it is also one of the most popular tourist attractions on the planet. However, sadly, half the coral in the reef has died since 2016. The Commonwealth and Queensland Government\'s Reef 2050 Long-Term Sustainability Plan therefore aims to protect the reef and ensure its future.&nbsp;</strong></p>', 'LhJPp31HOHwhtr1MEhULBcCCW.jpg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:30:39', '2020-01-20 03:30:39'),
(10, 8, 'Laboratory-Made CO2-Eating Bacteria Could Help Solve Climate Change, Says Scientists', '10~laboratory-made-co2-eating-bacteria-could-help-solve-climate-change-says-scientists', '<p><strong>The crew used \"metabolic rewiring\" to further convert the&nbsp;<em>E-coli\'s</em>&nbsp;food intake to make it similarly consume carbon dioxide to a plant. The rewiring included adding genes that metabolize CO2 and remove genes that usually process sugar compounds.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Study co-author Shmuel Gleizer, a Weizmann Institute of Science postdoctoral fellow, said he and his team wanted to see from an essential scientific perspective if such a significant transformation in the diet of bacteria is possible.</strong></p>', 'QGSFr5vvmln31E7PXzdJP0wlG.jpg', 4, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2020-01-20 03:31:33', '2020-01-20 03:31:33'),
